<m1><styl>RULERON<ql>
<styl>breakout,13p6<ql>
   <m0>A sampling of what Faith Popcorn views as some of the sizzling new social trends in <m0>Clicking, 16 Trends to Future Fit Your Life, Your Work, Your Business.<m0> <ep>
   (box)<m0> Anchoring: <m0>``Reaching back to our spiritual roots, taking what was comforting from the past in order to be securely anchored in the future.'' Examples: Soaring church attendance, the popularity of angels, yoga classes, bestsellers like <m0>The Celestine Prophecy.<m0> <ep>
  <m0>(box) FemaleThink:<m0> ``A new set of business and social values, encouraging us to shift marketing consciousness from the traditional goal-oriented, hierarchal models to the more caring, sharing familial ones.'' Example: Saturn car dealers with child-care areas, The Body Shop's no-animal-testing policy.<ep>
 <m0>(box) Mancipation: <m0>``A NewThink that goes beyond being `strictly business' and warmly embraces the freedom of being an individual.'' Examples: Unisex fragrances like CK, male skirts, a Discover magazine article in which the male writer explored the medical possibilities of breast-feeding his own children.<ep>
    <m0>(box) Icon toppling:<m0> ``A new socioquake has transformed mainstream America and the world, forcing us to question our monuments of business/government, the long accepted `pillars of society.' '' Examples: AT&T and massive corporate layoffs, <m0>Hard Copy<m0>  and its cousins airing society's dirtiest lingerie.<ep>
<m1><styl>cxon<ql>
<m2> <ql>
<m0>   (box) <m0>Pleasure Revenge: <m0>``Consumers, tired of all the rules and regulations, want to cut loose and have secret bacchanals with a bevy of forbidden fruits.'' Examples: Hebrew National hot dog sales are up, the red meat renaissance, the cigar craze, the spread of coffee shops.<ep>
